-- Starboard offers to take RealD private for $12/share
-- By Anya George Tharakan in Bangalore
-- Wed Oct 01, 2014 06:06PM EDT
-- None



Oct 1 (Reuters) - Activist investor Starboard Value LP said it proposed to acquire 3D technology licensor RealD Inc <RLD.N> for $12 per share.

The offer price represents a premium of about 29 percent to RealD stock's Wednesday close of $9.27 and values the company at about $540 million. (http://1.usa.gov/1rMY8tq) Starboard is the third-largest stakeholder in the company with a 9.9 percent stake.